The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning mechanism for incentivizing high-quality data in crowdsourcing, which involves designing an algorithm to estimate workers' labeling strategies and dynamically determining payments without accessing ground-truth labels. This work involves machine learning, optimization, and human-computer interaction, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.HC. Additionally, the paper uses Bayesian inference and Gibbs sampling, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.SI.
